bio.experienceSummary:
Exceptional with Children: 

Connecting, Engaging, and Creating Positive/Memorable Interactions. Naturally Connects with Kids! 

Babysitting Highlights:
- Have worked with 5 + families
- College Degree : Major in Finance ; Minor in History 
- Caregiving , driving, laundry, meal prep, homework, playtime, sports and activities 

As a caregiver, I'm passionate about nurturing children's development and well-being. With three years of experience. My calm and friendly nature allows me to connect easily with children, fostering trust and open communication.

From outdoor sports to educational games, I enjoy a wide range of activities that promote physical, mental, and emotional growth. My college degree further equips me with knowledge and skills to support children's holistic development.

I'm happy to assist with cooking, meal preparation, and light housekeeping tasks.

description.originalText: Jake is an amazing young man - I met him in our local community. He has worked with our family many times, and has also babysat our kids over the course of weekends when we went away. He is incredibly kind, honest and smart. I trust him 100% and recommend him highly.

bio.experienceSummary: Hello! My name is Jaida. I am soon going to soon graduate college with a majoring in criminology and minor in psychology. I love working with children and have the experienced of over 6+ years in working at a school. I find it very important for me to build a connection with the young ones assuring them with trust and respect I promise to deliver everyday. Singing, dancing, acting, and teaching will be implemented creating a fun learning environment!

description.originalText: Jaida was absolutely wonderful! My husband and I were in NYC for a few days and needed a babysitter for our 13-month-old daughter while we attended a late-night event. From the moment Jaida arrived, she made us feel completely comfortable. She showed up early, asked all the right questions, and our daughter instantly took to her, which was such a relief since this was our first time leaving her with a sitter. Jaida kept us updated throughout the night with thoughtful messages, which truly helped us relax and enjoy our time out. She is warm, compassionate, and truly thoughtful—everything we could have possibly hoped for in a sitter. We wholeheartedly recommend her to anyone seeking a dependable, nurturing, and trustworthy individual to look after their little one. She’s amazing!

bio.experienceSummary: Hello! My name is Yasmyne. I've been working with kids since I was about 13 years old. I started my caregiver journey with my younger siblings, when the parents needed me, I was always there to help. Further into my journey, I began babysitting for various friends and family. Now, I'm both a nanny and babysitter and have worked with several families within NYC. Most of my experience has been working with children from newborn to school age; I do, however, have some experience with teens. So, about myself, I enjoy going out for walks in the park and visiting the museum and library. I love singing, dancing, listening to music, and reading books to the kids. I am also an artist and enjoy creating anything possible in my free time, even when I'm with the kids. Overall, I'm the perfect nanny for families who prefer their kids to be unplugged and away from technology. I always do my best to redirect and find positive outcomes not only for the child but the family as a whole!

description.displayText: As a first time mom, finding someone to care for our baby girl seemed daunting. Then Yasmyne applied. Throughout our time together (going on 6 months!), she's been a pleasure to work with. She's reliable, kind and courteous. Most importantly, our daughter adores her!! When Yasmyne walks though the door, the smile on our daughter's face assures us we've found an amazing caregiver!!

bio.experienceSummary:
Dear all, I go by River she/they ( Legal name is Katherine)! I am 26 years old with degrees in psychology and theater. In psychology my focus has been on development through music and vocal psychotherapy and theater my focus has been in acting. All my life my greatest love and passion is taking care of all beings. I have had tremendous amount of background in babysitting starting very young and working at day cares, elderly homes, animal rescues, after school day care, and abroad orphanages. Caring for others is a true honor and privilege to me. I love being a babysitter and nanny because I love to take care, set by example, learn, grow, play, and create with children. With my background of arts and psychology I love to infuse playing, learning, and creativity into one!

It would be my privilege to be trusted with those you love.

I would really cherish the opportunity to speak more! 
Big big hugs! 
River

Brooklyn located nanny/sitter with 10+ years of childcare experience. Graduated from NYU in May 2023 with a degree in vocal performance. Throughout high school and then college, Ive worked as a babysitter, and then nanny for multiple families. I've worked with children, toddlers, and infants. I've had experience with newborns as young as one week and kids as old as 12 years. I've watched kids of all ages, from all backgrounds with all different kinds of interests. I also have experience with children with special needs. I love music and singing, and have so much fun including this into my work! My most recent jobs are working in a daycare teacher in a pre-k setting with 3-4-year-olds. I left my daycare job to become a nanny, and currently I work for a wonderful family in Brooklyn with a 3-year-old girl and 11-month-old boy, who I have watched since he was a newborn. I am looking for jobs to supplement my income since I only work about 25 hours a week!

description.originalText: Hannah took care of our little daughter while we were in nyc and it was extremely professional and efficient . We are def using Hannah for future trips .

bio.experienceSummary:
I am 26 and have 8+ years of babysitting all ages. I am super organized and love helping families out with their kids! Below are some things I am able to offer:
- clean dishes, laundry, meal prep, and tidying up around the house
- engage in arts & crafts, games, reading, sports
- assist with homework & studying

I am originally from Washington State, I spent my earlier education in a Spanish Immersion Program, graduating from High School with my Seal of Biliteracy in Spanish and a love for the language and culture as well. I have worked as a babysitter, nanny, and tutor to children ages ranging from 3 months to 15 years old, as well as children with learning disabilities such as ADHD and Down Syndrome. My responsibilities as a babysitter include productively managing the needs and environment of the children I care for alongside teaching and conversing in Spanish with some, and taking time to provide understanding and patient care to families. I often perform many housekeeping duties alongside the care I provide, preparing and serving meals, as well as facilitating creative and playful activities.

I am a young college grad living in NYC who has been working with kids since the 8th grade. I love working with kids and have extensive experience with multiple kids, homeschooling and tutoring, fitness and working with children with disabilities. I am excited to find a new position here in the city!

I am a warm, energetic and friendly person who enjoys working with kids and cares about their development. I believe in the importance of the nurturing and support children receive, as it shapes their experiences and minds. I am a nerd, and would love to help your kids with their homework or any learning generally. I have been babysitting since high school and also love to play with and entertain kids too. I would also be happy to cook and do some light housekeeping, organizing and straightening up..

Hi families, I'm from Colombia, I'm 26 years old. I'm responsible, patient, respectful, organized, tidy and most important thing I love kids. I was an AuPair for 2 years taking exceptional care of 2 beautiful kids (2 and 3 years old). I started babysitting since I was 21 years old, working for summer camps, foundations and schools in Colombia, bringing care to kids of all ages. I have good recommendations, and long experience with kids. I love music, movies, drawing and nature. One thing you should know about me is that my first language is Spanish. My skills include professionalism, decision-making and confidence

description.originalText:
Maria has been an extraordinary nanny for our 2 y/o, blending professionalism with a genuinely caring approach. Her innate ability to anticipate our child's needs, coupled with her flexibility in adapting to our changing schedules, has been a significant relief for us.
Maria consistently went above and beyond in her duties, engaging our child in both fun and educational activities that sparked a love for learning early on. Her intuitive understanding and emotional connection with our child, while maintaining a professional stance, were truly commendable. I cant recommend her enough!
